g.title: is_dest_reference
g.text: Is the destination type a reference type?

g.title: list_has_designated_initializer
g.text: Does the braced-init-list contain a designated-initializer-list?

g.title: is_char_arr_init
g.text: Is the destination type a char[] or a char*_t[]?

g.title: reference_dest_type_defn
g.text: Let the destination type be "reference to cv1 T1".

g.title: is_char_arr_literal_init
g.text: Is the initializer a string literal?

g.title: is_dest_array
g.text: Is the destination type an array?

g.title: string_literal_verify_kind
g.text: Verify array type and literal type match.

g.title: value_is_class
g.text: Is the type a class type?

g.title: is_dest_class_type
g.text: Is the destination type a class type?

g.title: array_k_definition
g.text: Let k be the number of elements in the initializers expression list.'

g.title: is_source_class_type
g.text: Is the source type a class type?

g.title: array_is_unsized
g.text: Is destination type an array of unknown bound?

g.title: array_sized_n_defn
g.text: Let n be the array size of the destination type.

g.title: array_initialize_first_k
g.text: Copy-initialize the first k array elements from the expressions in the initailizer.

g.title: class_source_consider_conversion_functions
g.text: Use overload resolution to select the best applicable conversion function.

g.title: standard_conv_seq_initialization_head
g.text: The object is initialized as follows:

g.title: standard_conv_seq_do_init
g.text: Initialize the object using the value of the initializer expression, using a standard conversion sequence if necessary, not considering any user-defined conversions.

g.title: nullptr_to_bool_init
g.text: The bool is initialized to false.

g.title: class_is_initializer_prvalue_same_class
g.text: Is the source type the same as the destination type (up to cv-qualification)?

g.title: class_initialize_by_prvalue
g.text: Use the prvalue to initialize the destination object.

g.title: class_is_copy_init_same_class
g.text: Is the source type the same class as the destination type (up to cv qualification)?

g.title: class_consider_constructors
g.text: Enumerate constructors and select best through overload resolution.

g.title: class_is_copy_init_derived_class
g.text: Is the source type a derived class of the destination type?

g.title: class_user_defined_conv_overload_resolution
g.text: Use overload resolution to select the best user-defined conversion that can convert from the source type to the destination type or (when a conversion function is used) to a derived class thereof.

g.title: class_constructors_use_selected
g.text: Use the selected constructor to initialize the object, using the expression or expression-list as argument(s).

g.title: class_is_aggregate
g.text: Is the destination type an aggregate class?

g.title: class_aggregate_is_initializer_expr_list
g.text: Is the initializer a parenthesized expression-list?

g.title: class_aggregate_paren_n_defn
g.text: Let n be the number of elements in the aggregate.

g.title: class_aggregate_paren_k_defn
g.text: Let k b ethe number of elements in the initializers expression list.'

g.title: class_aggregate_paren_initialize_first_k
g.text: Copy-initialize the first k elements from the expression list.

g.title: class_aggregate_paren_initialize_rest
g.text: Use default member initializer or value-initialize the remaining elements.

g.title: class_user_defined_conv_is_possible
g.text: Is the conversion ambiguous or impossible?

g.title: class_user_defined_conv_do_conversion
g.text: Call the selected function with the initializer-expression as its argument.

g.title: class_user_defined_conv_initialize
g.text: Direct-initialize the destination object with the result of the conversion.

g.title: string_literal_initialize_first
g.text: Initialize the first elements of the array with successive values from the string literal.

g.title: string_literal_has_too_many
g.text: Are there more initializers than array elements?

g.title: string_literal_initialize_rest
g.text: Zero-initialize the remaining elements of the array (if any).

g.title: class_source_conversion_is_impossible
g.text: Is the conversion impossible or ambiguous?

g.title: class_source_initialize
g.text: Use the result of the conversion to convert the initializer to the object being initialized.

g.title: standard_conv_seq_is_bitfield
g.text: Is the object to be initialized a bit-field?

g.title: standard_conv_seq_is_bitfield_in_range
g.text: Is the value representable by the bit-field?

g.title: standard_conv_seq_bitfield_imp_def
g.text: The value of the bit-field is implementation-defined.

g.title: reference_source_type_defn
g.text: Let the source type be "cv2 T2".

g.title: reference_is_dest_lval
g.text: Is the destination type an lvalue reference?

g.title: reference_dest_is_lval_non_const
g.text: Is the destination an lvalue reference to a non-const type?

g.title: reference_lvals_is_compatible
g.text: Is cv1 T1 reference-compatibile with cv2 T2?

g.title: reference_dest_is_volatile
g.text: Is the destinations referenced type volatile-qualified'

g.title: reference_lvals_compatible_bind
g.text: The destination reference is bound to the initializer lvalue (or appropriate base).

g.title: reference_dest_lval_source_class_is_convertible
g.text: Is T2 convertible to an lvalue of type cv3 T3 such that cv1 T1 is reference-compatible with cv3 T3?

g.title: reference_class_select_conversion
g.text: Select the best applicable conversion function.

g.title: reference_class_do_initialization
g.text: The destination reference is bound to the result of the conversion (or appropriate base).

g.title: reference_rval_conv_source_is_function_lval
g.text: Is the initializer a function lvalue?

g.title: reference_rval_conv_source_rval_or_function_is_ref_compat
g.text: Is cv1 T1 reference-compatible with cv2 T2?

g.title: reference_rval_conv_bind_direct
g.text: The converted initializer is the value of the initializer.

g.title: reference_rval_conv_is_converted_prval
g.text: Is the converted initializer a prvalue?

g.title: reference_rval_conv_source_class_convertible_target
g.text: Is the initializer convertible to an rvalue or function lvalue of type "cv3 T3"
where "cv1 T1" is reference-compatible with "cv3 T3"?

g.title: reference_rval_conv_bind_converted
g.text: The converted initializer is the result of the conversion.

g.title: reference_rval_conv_prval_adjust_type
g.text: Its type T4 is adjusted to "cv1 T4".

g.title: reference_rval_conv_bind_glval
g.text: The destination reference is bound to the resulting glvalue.

g.title: reference_temp_implicit_conv
g.text: The initializer expression is implicitly converted to a prvalue of type "cv1 T1".

g.title: reference_temp_user_defined_conv
g.text: Consider user-defined conversions for the copy-initialization of an object of type "cv1 T1" by user-defined-conversion.

g.title: reference_temp_user_defined_conv_is_ill_formed
g.text: Would the non-reference copy-initialization be ill-formed?

g.title: reference_temp_user_defined_conv_direct_initialize
g.text: The result of the call to the conversion function, as described by non-reference copy-initialization, is used to direct-initialize the reference. For the direct-initialization, user-defined conversions are not considered.

g.title: reference_temp_implicit_conv_materialize_bind
g.text: The reference is bound to the result.

g.title: reference_temp_implicit_conv_materialize_is_cv_okay
g.text: Is cv1 more qualified than cv2?

g.title: reference_temp_implicit_conv_materialize_is_dest_rval
g.text: Is the destination an rvalue reference?

g.title: value_has_dflt_ctor
g.text: Does the type have a default constructor?

g.title: value_is_array
g.text: Is the type an array type?

g.title: value_has_deleted_dflt_ctor
g.text: Does the type have a deleted default constructor?

g.title: value_has_user_dflt_ctor
g.text: Does the type have a user-provided default constructor?

g.title: value_check_default
g.text: The semantic constraints for default-initialization are checked.

g.title: value_has_nontrivial_dflt_ctor
g.text: Does the type have a non-trivial default constructor?

g.title: list_designated_initalizer_is_aggregate
g.text: Is the type an aggregate class?

g.title: list_is_aggregate_class
g.text: Is the type an aggregate class?

g.title: list_designated_initializer_are_identifiers_valid
g.text: Do the designators form a subsequence of the ordered idenitifiers in the direct non-static data members of the type?

g.title: list_aggregate_is_list_singleton
g.text: Does the initializer list have a single element?

g.title: list_is_type_char_array
g.text: Is the type a character array?

g.title: aggregate_determine_elements
g.text: Determine the elements of the aggregate.

g.title: list_aggregate_singleton_is_type_valid
g.text: Does the sole element have type "cv U"
where U is the initialized type or a type derived of it?

g.title: list_char_array_is_singleton
g.text: Does the iniitializer list have a single element?

g.title: list_aggregate_singleton_type_init_type
g.text: What is the type of initialization?

g.title: list_aggregate_singleton_type_copy
g.text: The object is copy-initialized from the sole element.

g.title: list_aggregate_singleton_type_direct
g.text: The object is direct-initialized from the sole element.

g.title: list_char_array_singleton_is_typed
g.text: Is that element an appropriately-typed string-literal?

g.title: list_empty_is_class
g.text: Is the destination type a class type?

g.title: list_dest_is_initializer_list
g.text: Is the type a specialization of std::initializer_list?

g.title: list_empty_has_default_constructor
g.text: Does the class have a default constructor?

g.title: list_is_class
g.text: Is the type a class type?

g.title: list_initializer_list_n_defn
g.text: Let N be the number of elements in the initalizer list.

g.title: list_class_ctors
g.text: Constructors are considered, and the best match is selected through overload resolution.

g.title: list_initializer_list_materialize_array
g.text: Where type is std::initializer_list<E>, a prvalue of type "array of N const E" is materialized.

g.title: list_initializer_list_init_array
g.text: Each element of the array is copy-initialized with the corresponding element of the initializer list.

g.title: list_initializer_list_is_narrowing
g.text: Is a narrowing conversion required to initialize any of the elements?

g.title: list_initializer_list_init_object
g.text: The initializer_list is constructed to refer to the materialized array.

g.title: list_class_is_narrowing
g.text: Is a narrowing conversion required to convert any of the arguments?

g.title: list_enum_is_fixed
g.text: Does the enumeration have fixed underlying type?

g.title: list_final_is_singleton
g.text: Does the initializer list have a single element?

g.title: list_enum_underlying_defn
g.text: Let U be the underlying type.

g.title: list_final_singleton_type_defn
g.text: Let E be the type of that element.

g.title: list_ref_prvalue_is_ref
g.text: Is the destination type a reference type?

g.title: list_enum_is_singleton
g.text: Does the initializer list have a single element?

g.title: list_enum_is_convertible
g.text: Can v be implicitly converted to U?

g.title: list_enum_is_narrowing
g.text: Is a narrowing conversion required to convert v to U?

g.title: list_enum_initialization
g.text: The object is initialized with the value T(u).

g.title: list_final_singleton_is_dest_ref
g.text: Is the destination type a reference?

g.title: list_final_singleton_is_dest_ref_related
g.text: Is the destination types referenced type reference-related to E?'

g.title: list_final_singleton_type
g.text: What is the type of initialization?

g.title: list_final_singleton_direct
g.text: The destination is initialized by direct-initialization from the element.

g.title: list_final_singleton_copy
g.text: The destination is initialized by copy-initialization from the element.

g.title: list_final_singleton_is_narrowing
g.text: Is a narrowing conversion required to convert the element to the destination type?

g.title: list_ref_prvalue_type_is_unknown_bound
g.text: Is the destination type an array of unknown bound?

g.title: list_ref_prvalue_type_unknown_bound
g.text: The type of the prvalue is the type of x in U x[] H, where H is the initializer list.

g.title: list_ref_prvalue_type_normal
g.text: The type of the prvalue is the type referenced by the destination type.

g.title: list_ref_prvalue_init_prvalue
g.text: The prvalue initializes a result object by copy-list-initialization.

g.title: list_ref_prvalue_init_ref
g.text: The reference is direct-initialized by the prvalue.

g.title: aggregate_elements_type
g.text: What is the type of the aggregate?

g.title: aggregate_elements_array
g.text: The elements are the array elements in increasing subscript order.

g.title: aggregate_elements_class
g.text: The elements are the direct base classes in declaration order, followed by the direct non-static data members that are not members of an anonymous union, in declaration order.

g.title: aggregate_explicit_is_designated
g.text: Is the initializer list a designated-initializer-list?

g.title: aggregate_explicit_desginated_is_class
g.text: Is the aggregate of class type?

g.title: aggregate_explicit_is_init_list
g.text: Is the initializer list an initializer-list (i.e. does it have at least one element)?

g.title: aggregate_explicit_designated_are_designators_valid
g.text: Does each designators identifier name a direct non-static data member of that class?

g.title: aggregate_explicit_init_list
g.text: The explicitly initialized elements are the first elements of the aggregate, matching the number in the initializer list.

g.title: aggregate_explicit_empty
g.text: The initializer list is "{}", and there are no explicitly initialized elements.

g.title: aggregate_explicit_desginated
g.text: The explicitly initialized elements are those named by the designator's initializers (or those that contain the named elements)

g.title: aggregate_explicit_list_union_is_excess_explicit_init
g.text: Is there more than one explicitly initialized element?

g.title: aggregate_initialize_explicit
g.text: The explicitly initialized elements are initialized as follows:

g.title: aggregate_initialize_explicit_is_anon_union
g.text: Is the element an anonymous union object?

g.title: aggregate_initialize_explicit_copy_kind
g.text: What is the kind of brace initializer?

g.title: aggregate_initialize_explicit_union_is_duplicate_designator
g.text: Is there more than one designator that names a member of that anonymous union?

g.title: aggregate_initialize_explicit_copy_init_list
g.text: The element is copy-initialized from the corresponding initializer-clause.

g.title: aggregate_initialize_explicit_copy_designated
g.text: The element is initialized with the brace-or-equal initializer of the corresponding designated-initializer-clause.

g.title: aggregate_initialize_explicit_union_init
g.text: The anonymous union object is initialized by { D }, where D is the designated-initializer-clause naming a member of the anonymous union object.

g.title: aggregate_initialize_explicit_repeat_next
g.text: Repeat with the next explicitly initialized element.

g.title: aggregate_initialize_explicit_repeat_next->aggregate_initialize_nonexplicit_is_union
g.text: Once done with all explicitly initialized elements

g.title: aggregate_initialize_explicit_is_narrowing_checked
g.text: Is the initializer of the form "assignment-expression" or "= assignment-expression"?

g.title: aggregate_initialize_explicit_is_narrowing
g.text: Is a narrowing conversion required to convert the expression?

g.title: aggregate_initialize_nonexplicit_nonunion_has_dflt_mem_init
g.text: Does the element have a default member initializer?

g.title: aggregate_initialize_nonexplicit_union_empty_has_dflt
g.text: Does any variant member of the union have a default member initializer?

g.title: aggregate_initialize_nonexplicit_nonunion_dflt_mem_init
g.text: The element is initialized from that initializer.

g.title: aggregate_initialize_nonexplicit_nonunion_repeat_next
g.text: Repeat with the next non-explicitly-initialized element.

g.title: aggregate_initialize_nonexplicit_nonunion_copy_init
g.text: The element is copy-initialized from an empty initializer list.

g.title: aggregate_initialize_nonexplicit_nonunion_repeat_next->aggregate_initialize_nonexplicit_nonunion_repeat_next__generated_done
g.text: Once done with all explicitly initialized elements

g.title: aggregate_initialize_nonexplicit_union_dflt_mem
g.text: That member is initialized from its default member initializer.

g.title: aggregate_initialize_nonexplicit_union_first_mem
g.text: The first member of the union (if any) is copy-initialized from an empty initializer list.
